      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add development trace UI",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a source-checkout-only development LLM trace recorder for full prompt/tool payload debugging.\n- Exposes `traces.capabilities`, `traces.list`, and `traces.get` Gateway methods behind explicit development flags, admin scope, and a strict direct-loopback Control UI grant.\n- Bridges Codex app-server turns into the dev trace store so local debugging shows the actual turn/start payload, available tools, streamed/final response events, and timing/byte metadata.\n- Adds a Phoenix-style Traces Control UI with a compact trace selector and a dominant detail pane for prompt messages, tool schemas/arguments, parameters, response text, and raw payload disclosures.\n- Forwards the tracing env flags through `pnpm gateway:watch` so the normal local tmux gateway workflow can actually run with dev tracing enabled.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts -t \"fires llm_input, llm_output, and agent_end hooks for codex turns\" --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/styles/components.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/gateway-watch-tmux.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.ts ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts src/plugin-sdk/diagnostic-runtime.ts src/infra/llm-dev-tracing.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check scripts/gateway-watch-tmux.mjs src/infra/gateway-watch-tmux.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts ui/src/styles/components.css ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n- `pnpm ui:build`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Development-only tracing UI shows captured LLM prompt payloads, tool schemas, invocation parameters, response events, and raw request/response JSON while remaining disabled outside an explicit source-checkout loopback debugging session.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Control UI Playwright/Chromium E2E server with mocked Gateway WebSocket responses, plus the actual local Gateway restarted from branch tip `37e7960` with `OPENCLAW_DEV_TRACING_UI=1`, `OPENCLAW_DEV_TRACE_LLM_PAYLOADS=1`, and `OPENCLAW_DEV_TRACE_LLM_RESPONSE=1` via `pnpm gateway:watch`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Captured a Playwright browser recording through the mocked Traces route, then used `agent-browser` against the real dashboard to send a live `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` provider prompt: `For final tracing UI validation after restart, reply exactly: trace UI final restarted gateway proof 86492`. After the provider response completed, captured the real Traces UI with Playwright video and screenshots.\n\nEvidence after fix: Mocked visual proof is in `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/tracing-ui-selector-polish/`. Final branch-tip live proof is in `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/tracing-ui-final-live/`, including `final-live-tracing-ui.webm`, `final-live-readable-top.png`, `final-live-response.png`, `final-live-raw-expanded.png`, and `final-live-proof.json`.\n\nObserved result after fix: The restarted gateway (`OpenClaw 2026.5.22 (37e7960)`) produced a completed Codex trace with readable prompt panels, readable response text, 17 captured tools, concrete request/response byte counts, and raw request/response disclosures. The final proof reports `completed: true`, `detailWiderThanList: true`, `horizontalOverflow: false`, `promptVisible: true`, `responseVisible: true`, `rawRequestAvailable: true`, `rawResponseAvailable: true`, `rowHasDuration: false`, and `rowHasRequestBytes: false`.\n\nWhat was not tested: `agent-browser record` specifically; `ffmpeg` is not installed in this environment, so the final screen recording uses Playwright `recordVideo`. A local autoreview subprocess also stalled earlier with no output after more than 14 minutes, so the final bridge/UI diff received focused manual review plus the automated checks above.\n",
